Nigerian youngster, Victor Osimhen has been linked with a move to Dutch club, AFC Ajax. According to Owngoalnigeria, the 19-year-old striker may be on his way to Amsterdam when he ends his loan spell at Charleroi. Osimhen is on loan from Wolfsburg until next summer and has been spectacular at Charleroi, scoring 7 goals in 13 games. Osimhen started his career at the Ultimate Strikers Academy, in Lagos before representing Nigeria at the 2015 FIFA U-17 World Cup. After a stellar performance at the showpiece, Osimhen caught the attention of VfL Wolfsburg, he officially joined the club in January 2017 on a three-and-a-half-year deal.